<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - MANIFOLDS AND EXHAUST GAS RECIRCULATION (EGR) - Removal - Intake
        Manifold and EGR Cooler
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>Intake Manifold and EGR Cooler</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Before removing intake manifold, remove the following components:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Fuel filter housing and lines</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>VGT</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
                <para>See "Fuel System" and "Electronically Controlled VGT" sections for removal procedures.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields to protect eyes. Limit
                    air pressure to 207 kPa (30 psi).
                </para>
            </warning>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, blow out or vacuum dirt and debris under the intake manifold. This
                    prevents dirt and debris from entering intake ports when the manifold is removed.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2350317.1" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd15/d1520.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 72. Intake heat shield mounting nuts (right side)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two M6 x 1 intake heat shield nuts located on the right side of the intake
                manifold.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350318" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd14/d1410.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 73. Intake manifold bolts and studs</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt (M6 x 95 dog point) (13)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt (M6 x 95) stud (3)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt (M6 x 55 x 20) stud (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 13 M6 x 95 bolts and three M6 x 95 studs securing the intake manifold. Do not remove
                two M6 x 55 x 20 studs .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Do not remove two M6 x 55 x 20 studs .</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350318.5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd05/d0511.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 74. EGR cooler coolant coupling</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Flat edge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dual index marks</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Single index mark</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Recess</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove EGR coolant inlet coupling, align dual index marks (if visible) or flat edge of
                coupling with index feature on coolant supply port cover .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350319" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd14/d1415.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 75. Removal of EGR coolant inlet coupling from coolant supply port</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Index feature on EGR coolant supply cover</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Coolant supply port</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EGR coolant inlet coupling</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide EGR coolant inlet coupling away from coolant supply port.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2050399" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd15/d1527.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 76. V-clamp</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove V-clamp at EGR cooler assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350320" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd14/d1416.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 77. Removal of intake manifold and EGR cooler assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove, lift intake manifold assembly straight up.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The EGR cooler should remain attached to the intake manifold.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place Intake Port Covers over cylinder head intake ports .</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
